column102: RequirementText
The system shall provide a web-based interface to manage requests for new accounts, equipment and software access rights.
The system shall be accessible via Intranet.
It shall be possible for users who access the system from Intranet to be automatically logged in.
The system shall log activity information of every request during its full life cycle.
Historical activity information shall be accessible by Service Desk and administrators.
Initiator shall be able to view an overview of their requests.
Initiator shall be able to request the creation of a user account.
Initiator shall be able to request the modification of a user account.
Initiator shall be able to request the removal of a user account.
Initiator shall be able to submit requests on behalf of another person (Requester) for a user account (Recipient).
The account request form shall contain the following fields to be filled by the Initiator: Lastname, firstname, employee type, company
A new account request form shall contain the following fields to be filled by HR Administrator: SAP ID, employee number
A new account request form shall contain the following fields for ICT equipment request to be filled by the Initiator: PC need, keyboard layout type
The following fields shall be automatically set by the system: Date of request, initiator, requester
The Initiator shall be able to indicate that he wants to be informed when an account request status changes in the workflow.
The system shall send an email notification to the Initiator and Requester with the account request status when the status changes in the workflow, if that option has been activated
If an ID badge is requested and the period of access is not specified the system shall default it to contract end date
Upon the submission of an account or equipment request the system shall send an email notification to the respective manager.
The email notification shall contain a link to the application in order to approve or reject the request and the request details.
Account requests shall be approved or rejected by the selected manager.
The manager shall be able to indicate the reasons of rejection.
Upon approval by the manager the system shall send an email notification to HR Administrator.
The email notification sent to HR Administrator shall contain the request details and a link to the application in order to add further information
Upon rejection an email notification shall be sent to the Initiator and Requester containing the reasons of rejection.
Upon the submission of further information by HR Administrator the system shall send an email to the Initiator and Requester containing all request details.

Upon the submission of further information by HR Administrator the system shall send an email to ServiceDesk containing all request details. The subject shall include the label �Account� and the user�s last name.
Upon the submission of further information by HR Administrator the system shall send an email to ServiceDesk:
Initiator shall be able to request access to one or more items of a particular group.
Initiator shall be able to request the removal of access from one or more items of a particular group.
Initiator shall be able to make requests for another person (Recipient).
It shall be possible to submit an access request together with an account request.
Initiator shall be able to select the type of access requested for each item e.g. RO, RW, Admin.
Initiator shall be able to load a previously saved template containing a list of items and access rights.
Initiator shall indicate a justification for the request.
The Approval Officer of a group shall be able to view the list of Recipients in that group.
The Approval Officer of a group shall be able to request the removal of service access by selecting a Recipient from the list.
Initiator shall be able to save templates containing the selected items and access rights for future use.
Saved templates shall be only accessed by the owners.
Initiator shall be able to delete their own saved templates.
The system shall send an email notification to the Approval Officer of each item upon the submission of an access request.
The email notification sent to the Approval Officer shall contain a link to the application in order to approve or reject the request.
The Approval Officer shall be able to approve or reject the item access request.
The Approval Officer shall be able to indicate the reasons of rejection.
It shall be possible for another person to approve or reject the request on behalf of the Approval Officer if the email is forwarded.
The system shall log the name of the Approval Officer or the person approving on behalf.
Upon approval the system shall send an email to ServiceDesk containing the request details.
The �From:� address of the email sent to the ServiceDesk shall be the email address of Requester.
Upon rejection an email notification shall be sent to the Initiator and Recipient containing the reasons of rejection.
Requests to remove access from items by the Approval Officer shall not be subject to approval.
Upon the submission of a request to remove access by the Approval Officer, the system shall send an email notification to ServiceDesk containing the request details.
Administrators shall be able to add, update and remove groups.
Administrators shall be able to add, update and remove items to each of the groups.
Administrators shall be able to define the access rights of each item. e.g. RO, RW, Admin.
Administrators shall be able to define the Approval Officer of each item.
The request forms shall display a history log underneath in all stages of the workflow.
The history log shall identify the type of change, the actionee and date of change.
Users shall be able to see a list of requests created by themselves or on behalf of themselves.
Managers, Software Owners and HR Administrators shall be able to see a list of open requests addressed to them.
Service Desk shall be able to see a list of all requests.
It shall be possible to search service access requests based on its meta-data.
It shall be possible to search account requests based on its meta-data.
It shall be possible to search software requests based on its meta-data.
It shall be possible to search account extension requests based on its meta-data.
It shall be possible to search administration rights requests based on its meta-data.
Users shall be able to see the list of access rights granted to persons reporting to them (e.g. Reporting Officer).
Users shall be able to download a printable version of the list mentioned in Requirement 65.
The system shall send an automatic reminder at regular interval (configurable) to Managers, Software Owners and HR Administrators for all requests awaiting for approval.
Initiators shall be able to request software for themselves.
Initiators shall be able to make requests for another person (Recipient).
Administrators shall be able to update the list of software for each of the software category.
Administrators shall be able to update the list of software owners.
Upon submission of a software request the system shall send an email notification to Service Desk with the request details if the software does not require approval.
The Manager shall be able to approve or reject the software request.
The Manager shall be able to indicate the reasons of rejection.
Upon rejection by Manager, an email notification shall be sent to the Initiator and Recipient containing the reasons of rejection.
Upon approval by manager, the system shall Send an email notification to Service Desk with the request details if the software does not require approval by the software owner.
The software owner shall be able to approve or reject the software request.
The software owner shall be able to indicate the reasons of rejection.
Upon rejection by the software owner, an email notification shall be sent to the Initiator and Recipient containing the reasons of rejection.
Upon approval by the software owner, the system shall send an email notification to Service Desk with the request details.
Initiators shall be able to request an account extension for themselves.
Initiators shall be able to make requests for another person (Recipient).
Initiators shall be able to make requests on behalf of a Requester. e.g. a secretary on behalf of a technical officer.
The user shall enter the following data in the request form: Recipient and extension date
Upon submission of an account extension request, the system shall Send an email notification to manager with request details for approval
The manager shall be able to approve or reject the account extension request.
The manager shall be able to indicate the reasons of rejection.
Upon rejection by manager, an email notification shall be sent to the Initiator and Recipient containing the reasons of rejection.
Upon approval by manager, the system shall send an email notification to Service Desk with the request details
Initiators shall be able to request administration rights for themselves only.
Initiator shall be automatically set as Requester and Recipient.
Initiators shall not be able to make administration rights requests on behalf of a Requester or a Recipient.
It shall be possible to request one of the following administration rights subtypes: Software installation only or full administration rights
The request form shall include the following mandatory fields: initiator, requester, justification, duration.
The request form shall display the Terms of Use.
It shall be possible for system administrators to configure the maximum validation period for each of the request subtypes.
It shall be possible for system administrators to configure the text displayed in Terms of Use.
The system shall prevent a user of inserting a duration period higher than what is configure for the selected request subtype.
The system shall prevent a user of submitting the request without accepting the Terms of Use.
Upon submission of an administration rights request the system shall send an email notification to the Recipient�s manager with request details for approval
The manager shall be able to approve or reject the administration rights request.
The manager shall be able to indicate the reasons of rejection.
The approval form shall include a compliance statement.
It shall be possible for system administrators to configure the text of the compliance statement displayed in the approval form.
Upon rejection by manager, the system shall � Send an email notification to the Initiator and Recipient containing the reasons of rejection.
Upon approval of a 'Software Installation Administration Rights' request by manager, the system shall Send an email notification to Service Desk with the request details for implementation
Upon approval of a 'Full Administration Rights' request by manager, the system shall Send an email notification to the Approval Officer with request details for approval
The Approval Officer shall be able to approve or reject the administration rights request.
The Approval Officer shall be able to indicate the reasons of rejection.
Upon rejection by the Approval Officer, the system shall Send an email notification to the Initiator and Recipient containing the reasons of rejection.
Upon approval by the Approval Officer, the system shall Send an email notification to Service Desk with the request details for implementation
The system shall be accessible by Microsoft Internet Explorer version 8 upwards.
The system shall be compliant with the Intranet look and feel.
The user interface shall be in English.
The system shall show a progress indicator for long lasting operations.
The application shall use an Oracle Database as persistence backend.
The character encoding used in the persistence layer shall be UTF-8.
Access to the system shall be possible only after authentication.
The system shall use Active Directory for authentication and authorisation for all users accessing the system.
Security relevant events including the relationship between user actions and system activity shall be logged.
The system shall send e-mails via SMTP.
The system shall be designed to allow the extension of the use cases to at least SAP Request form
Initiator should be able to request equipment.
Initiator should be able to request equipment on behalf of the Requester.
Initiator should be able to print a request details independently of its status.
An Approval Officer should get a reminder after a configurable amount of days if he has not accepted/rejected the request.
A request should be automatically closed after a configurable amount of days if the Approval Officer has not approved or rejected.
The Initiator and the Requester should be informed via email if the request was automatically closed.
The Approval Officer should be able to change the requested access rights of each item.
The Approval Officer should be able to get an overview of the requests with their status.
The Approval Officer should be able to view the list of items in charge.
Administrators should be able to define the process for an automatic configuration of each item.
Administrators should be able to configure the number of days after which Approval Officers are reminded of their requests awaiting approval.
Administrators should be able to configure the number of days after which open requests are automatically closed.
The system should support the definition of an automatic configuration process for each item.
Service Desk should be able to trigger the automatic configuration of items defined with an automatic configuration process.
Upon the successful execution of an automatic configuration the request should be flagged as executed.
Upon the successful execution of an automatic configuration an email notification should be sent to Service Desk.
